# DS Component Test Strategy

Use this rule when adding tests to a Design System component in `packages/ui`.

## Project structure

```
packages/
  ui/                     → @ds-12/ui
    src/components/[name]/  ← component source
    tests/                ← package-level unit tests (optional)
apps/
  storybook/
    src/stories/[name]/[name].stories.tsx  ← visual + interaction tests
    .storybook/           ← Storybook config
    vite.config.ts        ← Vitest browser project for story tests
```

Components live in `packages/ui`. Stories live in `apps/storybook` and import via subpath exports (`@ds-12/ui/button`, etc.).

## Responsibility split

| Concern | Storybook (`apps/storybook`) | Vitest (`packages/ui`) |
|---|---|---|
| Visual render | ✓ | ✗ |
| User interaction flow | ✓ | ✗ |
| Accessibility (a11y) | ✓ | ✗ |
| Custom hooks logic | ✗ | ✓ |
| Utility functions | ✗ | ✓ |
| CVA conditional logic | ✗ | ✓ (only when non-trivial) |
| Edge cases non-visual | ✗ | ✓ |

## When to write Storybook tests

Always add interaction + a11y coverage in `apps/storybook/src/stories/[name]/[name].stories.tsx` for every component.

Follow `ds-storybook-testing` for story patterns. Keep existing visual stories (`Default`, variant stories, `AllVariants`) and add dedicated interaction stories with `play` functions. Run interaction tests from the Storybook UI; CI uses Chromatic for visual regression.

## When to write Vitest unit tests

Only when the component has:

- **Custom hooks** — test logic in isolation via `renderHook`
- **Utility functions** — test pure functions directly (e.g. `get-pagination-items.ts`)
- **CVA variant logic** — only if it contains conditionals beyond simple class mapping

Do NOT write Vitest tests for:

- Pure render output
- DOM interactions
- A11y attributes
- Visual states

### File location

Place unit tests next to the source file or under `packages/ui/tests/`:

```
packages/ui/src/components/pagination/get-pagination-items.test.ts   ← preferred for utils
packages/ui/tests/index.test.ts                                      ← package smoke tests
```

### Vitest patterns

Use Vite+ test imports:

```ts
import { expect, test } from "vite-plus/test";
```

**Utility function** (real example from this repo):

```ts
// get-pagination-items.test.ts
import { expect, test } from "vite-plus/test";
import { getPaginationItems } from "./get-pagination-items.ts";

test("returns all pages when totalPages <= 5", () => {
  expect(getPaginationItems(1, 3)).toEqual([
    { type: "page", page: 1 },
    { type: "page", page: 2 },
    { type: "page", page: 3 },
  ]);
});

test("returns empty array when totalPages <= 0", () => {
  expect(getPaginationItems(1, 0)).toEqual([]);
});
```

**Custom hook** (when a component exposes one):

```ts
import { expect, test } from "vite-plus/test";
import { renderHook, act } from "@testing-library/react";
import { useChipGroup } from "./useChipGroup.ts";

test("should toggle chip selection", () => {
  const { result } = renderHook(() => useChipGroup());
  act(() => result.current.toggle("active"));
  expect(result.current.selected).toContain("active");
});
```

**CVA conditional logic** (only when needed):

```ts
import { expect, test } from "vite-plus/test";
import { buttonVariants } from "./index.tsx";

test("should include loading modifier when loading", () => {
  expect(buttonVariants({ variant: "primary", size: "md" })).toContain("button-primary-md");
});
```

## Running tests

This repo uses Vite+ (`vp`), not Turbo.

```bash
# Unit tests for @ds-12/ui
cd packages/ui && vp test

# Format, lint, typecheck, and test everything
vp check && vp run -r test
```

Root `package.json` uses `vp run -r test` to run tests across workspace packages.

## Output checklist

- [ ] Story file exists at `apps/storybook/src/stories/[name]/[name].stories.tsx`
- [ ] Component lives under `packages/ui/src/components/` (resolved by Storybook's `@ds-12/ui` alias)
- [ ] Interaction + a11y stories added per `ds-storybook-testing`
- [ ] Vitest unit tests added only if hooks or utils exist
- [ ] `vp check && vp test` pass in affected packages
